The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Hero Group on list of victims 
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                      Hero Group on list of victims 
                            
	New Delhi, Dec. 30 (PTI): The Hero Group today said it is a victim of the estimated Rs 300 -crore Citibank fraud.        
	Some of the Hero Group entities, along with some others, are victims of the fraud conducted through one of the Citi branches in Gurgaon, it said in a statement.        
	An inquiry is on and the next step will be decided after it ends, the group added.        
	Shivraj Puri, a manager with the bank, was arrested today for swindling wealthy clients of crores.        
	A police officer supervising the case said most of the clients who invested in the trust scheme that Puri promised would yield unusually high returns belonged to the Hero Group.        
	Naveen Munjal of Hero Exports alone had given around Rs 50 crore to Puri for investment, the officer said.        
	Gurgaon police commissioner S.S. Deswal said of the Rs 300 crore swindled, Rs 200 crore belonged to the banks corporate clients and Rs 100 crore to moneyed individuals.                                                                                                                                                          
